TcRuntimeType.description: Cm1ChangeHistoryElement is a runtime business object used to present a row of information in a change history table. Cm1ChangeHistoryElement encapsulates the results of navigation of several relations to present the change history of a business object. Cm1ChangeHistoryElement includes details on the authorizing ChangeNoticeRevision object, impacted and solution objects, incorporation details of competing ChangeNoticeRevision objects, and related markup object. Cm1ChangeHistoryElement is used in Teamcenter Change Management Active Workspace area.

TcProperty.description: cm1SolutionItem is a string representation of the solution object's name. cm1SolutionItem identifies the solution ovject related to an element in the context of the business object's change history.

cm1SolutionImpactedItem is a string representation of the impacted object's name. cm1ImpactedItem identifies the impacted object related to an element in the context of the business object's change history.

cm1Markup is a string representation of the markup dataset object's name, which is getting incorporated by the change. cm1Markup identifies the markup dataset object related to an element in the context business object's change history.

cm1AuthorizingChangeNotice is a string representation of the ChangeNoticeRevision object's name. This property identifies the authorizing ChangeNoticeRevision object related to an element in the context business object's change history.

cm1Closure is a string representation of the ChangeNoticeRevision object's CMClosure attribute. cm1Closure identifies the authorizing object's CMClosure attribute state for an element in the context business object's change history.

cm1Maturity is a string representation of the ChangeNoticeRevision object's CMMaturity attribute. cm1Maturity identifies the authorizing ChangeNoticeRevision object's attribute state for an element in the context object's change history.
cm1Disposition is a string representation of the ChangeNoticeRevision object's CMDisposition attribute.

cm1IncorporatesChanges is a string representation of the solution object's name, which is getting incorporated by the object identified by the cm1AuthorizingChangeNotice property of this change history element.
cm1IncorporatedBy is a string representation of the ChangeNoticeRevision objects name, which is incorporating the object identified by the cm1SolutionItem property of this change history element.
cm1IncorporatedStatus is a string representation of the impacted object's cm0IncorporationStatus attribute related to an element in the context business object's change history.
cm1IncorporatedInto is a string representation of the solution object's name, which incorporated the modifications of another ChangeNoticeRevision.

Property cm1SolutionItemObject is a runtime object reference which represents the solution object whose display name is found in associated string property cm1SolutionItem of the same Cm1ChangeHistoryElement object.
Property cm1AuthorizingCNObject is a runtime object reference which represents the authorizing Change Notice revision.

OperationTemplate.description:
This operation creates and returns BOMEdit and BOMSupercedure objectss when solution objects and impacted objects are passed along with ChangeItemRevision. Passing impacted items is optional and if these are not passed, this operation will calculate impacted items by considering previous revision of solution items. This information is required in order to show structural changes made to the structure and display the information in change summary table in the Active Workspace application. It allows the user to generate BOMEdit objects by selecting a revised assembly ItemRevision (solution item) to runtime compare and generate the differences with its respective impacted item and persist those differences.

Use Cases:

Use Case 1: If isGenerateStructureEdit is true, then generate BOMEdit objects.

User associate impactedObjects(example ItemRevision A) as impacted relation of ChangeNoticeRevision and solutionObjects(example ItemRevision B) as solution relation of ChangeNoticeRevision. It creates CMSolutionToImpacted relation between ChangeNoticeRevision’s solution and impacted objects. The BOMEdit object is a record of a change made to a BOMLine object.

Use Case 2: If isGenerateStructureEdit is false, then just add to the solution.

User sends some objects as solution objects and impacted objects as null, then this operation will create CMHasSolution relation between ChangeNoticeRevision and solution objects.
OperationTemplate.name: Cm1::Soa::CmAws::Changes::generateStructureEdit
OperationTemplate.returnDescription:
List of BOMEdit and BOMSupercedure objectss.

The following partial errors may be returned:

520001 Object is not of type ChangeNoticeRevision.

520003 The creation of a Change Lineage has failed because either an invalid item, no solution item, or no impacted item is provided.

OperationParameter.description: A structure that has a list of solution and impacted objects, ChangeItemRevision and flag to indicate if structure edits needs to be generated.
OperationParameter.name: generateStructureEditInput

OperationTemplate.description:
Returns data required to populate change summary table on ChangeNoticeRevision summary page in the Active Workspace application. The change summary information is generated based on following objects.

1. CMSolutionToImpacted relation between ChangeNoticeRevision's solution and impacted objects. CMSolutionToImpacted is relation between solution and Impacted of ChangeNoticeRevision.
2. BOMEdit of all of the solution objects of ChangeNoticeRevision. The BOMEdit object is a record of a change made to a BOMLine object. The BOMEdit object consolidates every aspect of the change in a single object when the changes are saved.

The change summary table displays what’s changed in product as part of this particular ChangeNoticeRevision. It provides visual cues in red for modifications.

OperationTemplate.description:
This operation creates and returns BOMEdit and BOMSupercedure objects when solution objects and impacted objects are passed along with ChangeItemRevision. Passing impacted items is optional and if these are not passed, SOA will calculate impacted items by considering previous revision of solution items.This information is required in order to show structural changes made to the structure and display the information in change summary table in the Active Workspace application. It allows the user to generate BOMEdit objects by selecting a revised assembly ItemRevision (solution item) to runtime compare and generate the differences with its respective impacted item and persist those differences.

Use Cases:

Use Case 1: If isGenerateStructureEdit is true, then generate BOMEdit objects.

User associate impactedObjects(example ItemRevision A) as impacted relation of ChangeNoticeRevision and solutionObjects(example ItemRevision B) as solution relation of ChangeNoticeRevision. It creates CMSolutionToImpacted relation between ChangeNoticeRevision’s solution and impacted objects. The BOMEdit object is a record of a change made to a BOMLine object.

Use Case 2: If isGenerateStructureEdit is false, then just add to the solution.

User sends some objects as solution objects and impacted objects as null, then this operation will create CMHasSolution relation between ChangeNoticeRevision and solution objects.

Operation.description:
Returns data required to populate change summary table on ChangeNoticeRevision summary page in the Active Workspace application. The change summary information is generated based on following objects.

1. CMSolutionToImpacted relation between ChangeNoticeRevision's solution and impacted objects. CMSolutionToImpacted is relation between solution and Impacted of ChangeNoticeRevision.
2. BOMEdit of all of the solution objects of ChangeNoticeRevision. The BOMEdit object is a record of a change made to a BOMLine object. The BOMEdit object consolidates every aspect of the change in a single object when the changes are saved.

The change summary table displays what’s changed in product as part of this particular ChangeNoticeRevision. It provides visual cues in red for modifications.
Operation.name: getChangeSummaryData
Operation.returnDescription:
Row and Column information to render change summary table.
The following partial errors may be returned:

520001 Object is not of type ChangeNoticeRevision.
520008 The Object being expanded is not solution of ChangeNoticeRevision.
Operation.useCase:
Use Case:

Use Case 1: Change Summary for Revise Actions in Active Workspace

User associate an ItemRevison (Rev A) as impacted relation of ChangeNoticeRevision. User select the ItemRevision from Impacted folder of ChangeNoticeRevision and perform revise action and create new revision RevB. This action automatically associate new revision as solution of ChangeNoticeRevision and also create CMSolutionToImpacted relation between both revisions.
User select ChangeNoticeRevision and validate that change summary display a line indicating ItemRevision is revised from RevA to RevB as per of this particular change.

Use Case 1: Change Summary for Structure Changes in Active Workspace

User create a small assembly with few children and associate it with impacted of ChangeNoticeRevision. User select the ItemRevision from Impacted folder of ChangeNoticeRevision and perform revise action and create new revision RevB. This action automatically associate new revision as solution of ChangeNoticeRevision and also create CMSolutionToImpacted relation between both revisions.
User open new assembly in active workspace and perform modifications like Add new line, remove a line, Quantity Change, Replace line.

The change summary of the ChangeNoticeRevision should display above modification done in assembly

Operation.description: This operation performs a merge change on a source BOMLine object to target object in ACE split view where both the objects are part of a change Solution relation. Change tracking functionality in Change Manager track changes done on an assembly in BOMEdit or Solution relation. ACE uses these BOMEdit and Solution objects to render redlining data. This service operation provides a mechanism to merge these redline changes from source object to target object in ACE split view.
Operation.name: mergeRedLineChanges
Operation.returnDescription:
The ServiceData contains created, updated, or deleted objects along with partial error if any.

The following partial error may be returned:
•    43021: The given BOM View Revision cannot be modified. Please check your access rights.
•    233073: Change can’t be merged because the ChangeNotice is either closed or not in executing state.
•    233074: Merge operation can’t be performed. Please provide BOMLine or Selected Object as input for this operation.
Operation.useCase:
Use case: Merge redlining changes in ACE Split View.
User creates an assembly and revises it in change context ECN1. User performs changes like adding a new child or updates BOMLine properties on a revised assembly (target assembly). User again revises same assembly in another change context ECN2 and perform changes like adding a new child, replacing a child on this revised assembly (source assembly) and releases it. Now, in order to merge changes from released source assembly to target assembly, user opens a split view with source assembly and target assembly. User selects the redline in source assembly and invokes the Merge command, which will trigger service operation to merge changes from source to target objects. For example, if user selects add redline from source assembly and click on Merge, then BOMEdit object of type add will be created in context of target assembly and target change context ECN1.

ParameterInfo.description: MergeRedLineChangesInput object containing information required to merge redlining changes.

    • 233072: Revert operation can’t be performed. Please provide BOMLine or Selected Object as input for this operation.
Operation.useCase:
Use case 1: Revert redlining changes in ACE.
Users revise an assembly in a change context. After revision user opens the assembly in ACE. The user adds a new line, removes an existing line, updates few BOMLine properties on an existing line, and replaces a line. After performing these edits, changes are rendered as redlining in ACE. Users select one or all the modified lines and invoke the Revert Change command. This command should revert changes back to the original value and clear BOMEdit data automatically. For example, the newly added line after revert action should be removed from the assembly. The deleted line after revert action should be added back to the assembly. The updated property like Quantity, Sequence Number should be reverted to its original value.


Use case 2: Revert redlining changes in object location for revisable object (non-assembly).
When the user adds or removes relations from an object in a Change context, those actions are displayed as redlining data in the object-set table. After these actions when the user selects those redlining data and performs revert changes action which should revert those changes. For example, the added relation should be removed, and the removed relation should be added back.

ParameterInfo.description: A list of RevertRedlineInput containing information required to revert redlining changes.
